into my parents' bedroom.

248
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:12,316
They told me to sit
on the bed and be quiet.

249
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:15,710
They went to my mother's dressing table.

250
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:21,878
They painted their fingernails, they put
powder on their faces, they used lipstick.

251
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:26,158
They pulled hairs from their eyebrows
and brushed mascara on their lashes.

252
00:29:26,240 --> 00:29:30,836
They took off their socks and put
on my mother's silk stockings, panties.

253
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:37,439
They sauntered about the room looking
at the mirror, like beautiful women.

254
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:43,516
They laughed and kissed, they stroked
each other, they giggled. I was enchanted.

255
00:29:43,600 --> 00:29:45,591
They fed my enchantment.

256
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:51,956
They whispered to me
that it was our secret,

257
00:29:52,040 --> 00:29:56,955
that we would keep it in our hearts
forever, never reveal it.

258
00:29:57,040 --> 00:30:02,876
But that night at dinner I felt my father
staring at me, staring deep into me.

259
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:07,636
He chewed, swallowed, he put his
knife and fork down. He looked at me.

260
00:30:07,720 --> 00:30:11,395
My heart started to beat.
To thump, not to beat.

261
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:16,830
My father said "Tell me, Robert. What
have you been doing this afternoon?"

262
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:19,275
He knew.

263
00:30:19,360 --> 00:30:22,909
I knew he knew.
He was God. He was testing me.

264
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:28,996
So I told him. I told him all that my sisters
had done. I told him everything.

265
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:36,110
My mother was silent. My sisters'
faces were white. No one spoke.

266
00:30:37,560 --> 00:30:40,632
My father said "Thank you."
Finished his dinner.

267
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:45,111
After dinner my sisters and I
were called to my father's study.

268
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:50,957
They were beaten with a leather belt
without mercy. I watched this.

269
00:30:51,040 --> 00:30:54,476
A month later they took their revenge.

270
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:59,680
We children were again alone
in the house. Nanny was away.

271
00:30:59,760 --> 00:31:01,637
My youngest sisters...

272
00:31:01,720 --> 00:31:03,472
<i>Grazie.</i>

273
00:31:03,560 --> 00:31:07,030
...Alice and Lisa
came to me in the garden.

274
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:12,914
They said "Robert, come to the kitchen.
Eva and Maria have a treat for you."

275
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:15,309
I was suspicious, but I went.

276
00:31:15,400 --> 00:31:17,960
I was so...

277
00:31:18,040 --> 00:31:19,473
innocent.

278
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:22,916
On the table were two big bottles
of lemonade, cream cake,

279
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:25,594
cooking chocolate,
big box of marshmallows,

280
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:28,194
and Maria said
"Look, this is all for you."

281
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:31,352
"But first" Eva said
"you must drink some medicine."

282
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:39,120
"This is very rich food and it will protect
your stomach. Help you to enjoy it."

283
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:43,079
I was too greedy to question this.
I drank the medicine.

284
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:47,119
Then I ate the chocolate and the cake
and drank a bottle of lemonade.

285
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:51,716
They applauded and said that only a man
could drink a second bottle of lemonade.

286
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:56,828
It would be beyond my capabilities.
I said "Give it to me."

287
00:31:56,920 --> 00:32:02,040
I drank the second bottle and I finished
the chocolate, marshmallows and cake.

288
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:06,910
They said "Bravo", then
the kitchen began to spin round me

289
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:10,549
and I badly needed to go
to the lavatory.

290
00:32:12,080 --> 00:32:15,197
Suddenly Eva and Maria held me down

291
00:32:15,280 --> 00:32:19,114
and tied my hands together
with a long piece of rope behind my back

292
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:23,079
and dragged me into my father's study.

293
00:32:23,160 --> 00:32:27,073
They took the key from the inside,
slammed the door and locked it.

294
00:32:27,160 --> 00:32:33,838
"Bye-bye, Robert" they called.
"Now you are big Papa in his study."

295
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:39,790
I was locked in my revered,
my feared father's study

296
00:32:39,880 --> 00:32:44,158
where he received the diplomatic corps
of London, the elite of the worid.

297
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:50,315
And I puked and pissed and shat
all over my father's carpets and walls.

298
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:54,188
My father found me there.
He said "Robert..."

299
00:32:58,320 --> 00:33:00,788
"Have you been eating chocolate?"

300
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:06,352
Then he nearly killed me. Then
he didn't speak to me for six months.

301
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:10,833
I've never forgiven my sisters.

302
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:15,798
My only solace was my mother.

303
00:33:15,880 --> 00:33:18,075
I grew so thirsty at night,

304
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:22,438
she brought me a glass of water every
night and laid her hand upon my brow.

305
00:33:22,520 --> 00:33:25,512
She was... so tender.

306
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:30,068
When my father was away
I slept in her bed.

307
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:36,633
One afternoon, the wife of the
Canadian ambassador was invited to tea.

308
00:33:36,720 --> 00:33:40,110
She brought her daughter Caroline.

309
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:45,558
When my mother showed her mother our
garden we were left alone, the children.

310
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:51,237
Suddenly Eva said "Miss Caroline,
do you sleep with your mother?"

311
00:33:54,440 --> 00:33:56,476
Caroline said "No. Do you?"

312
00:33:56,560 --> 00:34:00,348
And Eva said "He does."

313
00:34:01,640 --> 00:34:05,872
And all my sisters giggled, and Caroline
looked at me and smiled and said:

314
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:09,157
"I think that's really awfully sweet."

315
00:34:09,240 --> 00:34:11,629
And she became my wife.

316
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:23,439
Not at that moment, of course. We were
both only... 11 years old at the time.

317
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:39,189
Where on earth are we?

318
00:34:41,200 --> 00:34:43,191
Do you know?

319
00:34:43,680 --> 00:34:46,478
Let me sit down. I've got such a...

320
00:34:47,520 --> 00:34:49,988
I've got such a headache.

321
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:54,315
Can you press the back of my neck?

322
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:56,391
Just there.

323
00:34:58,280 --> 00:35:01,158
- Oh, God. I'm going to...
- What?

324
00:35:15,960 --> 00:35:18,030
- Sorry.
- It's all right.

325
00:35:18,880 --> 00:35:22,236
I'm all right. I just have to sit down.

326
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:24,470
I can't walk any more.

327
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:28,631
Hold me.

328
00:35:34,040 --> 00:35:36,600
What a terrible man.

329
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:38,671
Who was he?

330
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:46,990
We're on holiday.

331
00:36:55,320 --> 00:36:57,117
Mary.

332
00:36:58,120 --> 00:37:00,111
Wake up.

333
00:37:02,120 --> 00:37:05,908
- Where are we?
- I don't know. Venice. Come on.

334
00:37:07,240 --> 00:37:09,231
Come on.

335
00:37:11,360 --> 00:37:13,351
You're a weight.

336
00:37:32,360 --> 00:37:34,351
I've been bitten.

337
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:36,635
Try not to scratch.

338
00:37:37,760 --> 00:37:39,955
I'm so thirsty.

339
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:45,239
You're going to have to
look after <i>me</i> today.

340
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:49,393
- Why? Did you look after me yesterday?
-

341
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:55,471
I'm so thirsty.

342
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:03,511
There's the waterfront.
Come on. There'll be a cafe.

343
00:38:16,640 --> 00:38:19,029
Let's go in the shade.

344
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:38,350
We'd like to order something to drink.

345
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:40,829
I will tell your waiter.

346
00:38:59,960 --> 00:39:02,679
I wonder how the children are.

347
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:06,834
Well, you spoke to them, when was it?

348
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:10,196
- Was it yesterday?
- How were they then?

349
00:39:11,080 --> 00:39:13,469
It's like a prison here.

350
00:39:15,240 --> 00:39:17,231
Let's go home.

351
00:39:20,320 --> 00:39:24,871
- The flight's paid for. It's not for five days.
- We could get another one.

352
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:27,952
Why do you want to go home?
Excuse me!

353
00:39:29,680 --> 00:39:31,750
I can't believe it. He's coming.

354
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:37,836
Bringing the children with us would have
made all the difference. To me, anyway.

355
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:43,948
- Signore?
- A jug of water, please. With ice.

356
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:47,237
- Water?
- Um... coffee.

357
00:39:47,320 --> 00:39:49,834
- Croissant? Eggs? Juice?
- No, just water.

358
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:53,959
- Let's go to the hotel and get water there.
- All right.

359
00:39:54,040 --> 00:39:57,237
He's probably bringing it anyway.

360
00:39:58,040 --> 00:40:00,634
I don't know why we came here.

361
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:05,388
We've been here before.
Why did we come again?

362
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:12,078
Actually, I remember why we came.

363
00:40:13,640 --> 00:40:17,428
We thought we'd find out
what to do, didn't we?

364
00:40:18,640 --> 00:40:21,234
What to do about you and me.

365
00:40:24,440 --> 00:40:26,032
Well?

366
00:40:27,920 --> 00:40:30,309
Have you found out?

367
00:40:31,400 --> 00:40:36,997
I haven't. I just want to go home.
To my own bed and my kids.

368
00:40:43,560 --> 00:40:45,551
Or maybe you have.

369
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:49,472
Maybe you have decided what you want.

370
00:40:50,840 --> 00:40:52,831
What you want to do.

371
00:40:55,920 --> 00:40:57,911
Have you?

372
00:41:04,040 --> 00:41:05,268
No.

373
00:41:16,520 --> 00:41:20,513
Oh, God. We should have
gone back to the hotel.

374
00:41:25,600 --> 00:41:28,194
He's missed us.

375
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:46,231
My friends.

376
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:50,792
- How are you both?
- Terrible. We slept in the street.

377
00:41:50,880 --> 00:41:52,871
Street?

378
00:41:52,960 --> 00:41:56,430
- After we left you...
- We didn't have a map.

379
00:41:56,520 --> 00:42:02,311
I'm horrified. It's entirely my fault. I kept
you late with wine and stupid stories.

380
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:05,631
- Don't scratch. It's not a question of that.
- It's my fault.

381
00:42:05,720 --> 00:42:10,157
And it's my responsibility to correct it.
You must come to my house.

382
00:42:10,240 --> 00:42:13,232
- Your coffee.
- <i>Senta. Lasci stare.</i>

383
00:42:13,320 --> 00:42:15,311
No, we have a hotel.

384
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:20,872
My house is a thousand times
more comfortable, peaceful, serene.

385
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:23,870
We take a taxi.

386
00:42:24,640 --> 00:42:25,868
Please.

387
00:42:26,920 --> 00:42:29,514
- What do you think?
- All right.

388
00:42:36,200 --> 00:42:38,191
The street!

389
00:45:07,440 --> 00:45:11,035
- Where are we?
- Robert brought us here.

390
00:45:13,680 --> 00:45:16,752
Robert. Where's he?

391
00:45:16,840 --> 00:45:18,831
I don't know.

392
00:45:22,880 --> 00:45:24,871
What time is it?

393
00:45:24,960 --> 00:45:26,552
Evening.

394
00:45:28,160 --> 00:45:31,948
- Did you sleep well?
- Yes, wonderfully.

395
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:42,714
How's your bite?

396
00:45:42,800 --> 00:45:44,950
It's gone.

397
00:45:45,040 --> 00:45:47,110
Where's my watch?

398
00:45:48,920 --> 00:45:50,990
Where's our clothes?

399
00:45:53,680 --> 00:45:55,875
Have you seen them?

400
00:46:08,320 --> 00:46:10,311
Not in there.

401
00:46:25,760 --> 00:46:27,830
Not in here.

402
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:29,592
No?

403
00:46:32,280 --> 00:46:35,352
Don't you think we ought to find them?

404
00:46:37,640 --> 00:46:40,200
- I feel good.
- I must find out what's going on.

405
00:46:40,280 --> 00:46:43,556
I just can't walk around here
stark bloody naked.

406
00:46:43,640 --> 00:46:47,918
I think there's a dressing gown
hanging up in there.

407
00:46:54,600 --> 00:46:56,989
I can't wear this. Look.

408
00:47:00,200 --> 00:47:03,237
Yes, you can. You look lovely.

409
00:47:04,040 --> 00:47:06,235
You look like a god.

410
00:47:07,200 --> 00:47:10,476
I think I'm going to have to
take you to bed.

411
00:47:10,560 --> 00:47:16,795
- This isn't a dressing gown, it's a nightie.
- You've no idea how good you feel in it.

412
00:47:16,880 --> 00:47:20,395
I can't walk around a stranger's house
dressed like this.

413
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:22,675
Not with an erection!

414
00:47:27,760 --> 00:47:29,751
Here. Put it on.

415
00:47:30,600 --> 00:47:33,068
Find out what's going on.

416
00:47:47,280 --> 00:47:49,271
How do I look?

417
00:48:05,240 --> 00:48:07,390
Hello.

418
00:48:07,480 --> 00:48:10,438
I'm Caroline, Robert's wife.

419
00:48:10,520 --> 00:48:13,512
- Well, you're looking rested!
- Hello.

420
00:48:13,600 --> 00:48:16,068
Come outside. It's nice.

421
00:48:21,160 --> 00:48:22,718
- Wow!
- Mm.

422
00:48:22,800 --> 00:48:27,874
It is beautiful, isn't it? I spend
as much time as possible out here.

423
00:48:27,960 --> 00:48:31,236
- I'm Mary Kenway.
- Yes, I know.

424
00:48:32,440 --> 00:48:35,238
- Come and sit down.
- Is this yours?

425
00:48:36,480 --> 00:48:38,311
Yes.

426
00:48:38,400 --> 00:48:40,152
I made it.

427
00:48:40,240 --> 00:48:43,596
I sometimes sit out here
and do embroidery. I like embroidery.

428
00:48:43,680 --> 00:48:45,796
It's lovely.

429
00:48:45,880 --> 00:48:49,668
- Would you like a biscuit? Take one.
- Thanks.

430
00:48:50,640 --> 00:48:55,316
You must be hungry. Robert wants you
to stay for dinner. He'll be back for dinner.

431
00:48:55,400 --> 00:48:59,473
He's gone to his bar.
A new manager starts there tonight.

432
00:48:59,560 --> 00:49:02,233
- <i>His</i> bar?
- Yes.

433
00:49:02,320 --> 00:49:06,029
You were there last night, weren't you?

434
00:49:06,120 --> 00:49:11,114
- He didn't say it was his bar.
- It's a kind of a hobby, I guess.

435
00:49:12,000 --> 00:49:16,790
But you know more about it than I do.
I've never been there.

436
00:49:21,160 --> 00:49:24,436
Have you done something to your back?

437
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:29,310
It helps to move. Sometimes
I just stand up and move about.

438
00:49:31,120 --> 00:49:34,192
- Are you fond of your friend?
- Colin?

439
00:49:36,360 --> 00:49:41,036
I hope you don't mind.
There's something I must tell you.

440
00:49:42,960 --> 00:49:46,839
While you were both asleep
I came in and looked at you both.

441
00:49:46,920 --> 00:49:52,916
I just sat on the chaise for half an hour.
I just sat there and looked at you both.

442
00:49:53,760 --> 00:49:55,352
Oh.

443
00:49:58,360 --> 00:50:02,433
Colin is very beautiful, isn't he?
Robert said he was.

444
00:50:02,520 --> 00:50:07,514
You are too, of course.
You both have such wonderful skin.

445
00:50:10,440 --> 00:50:12,317
Are you in love?

446
00:50:12,400 --> 00:50:14,391
Well, I...

447
00:50:15,360 --> 00:50:18,591
I do love him. I suppose.

448
00:50:18,680 --> 00:50:21,513
Not quite like when we first met.

449
00:50:21,600 --> 00:50:25,115
I trust him, really.
He's my closest friend.

450
00:50:25,200 --> 00:50:27,998
But what do you mean by "in love"?

451
00:50:29,160 --> 00:50:33,312
I mean that you'd do absolutely
anything for the other person.

452
00:50:33,400 --> 00:50:37,518
And you'd let them do
absolutely anything to you.

453
00:50:37,600 --> 00:50:39,511
Anything?

454
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:43,072
- If you're in love with somebody, you...
-

455
00:50:50,120 --> 00:50:54,875
- Hello!
- Colin, this is Caroline, Robert's wife.

456
00:50:54,960 --> 00:50:57,838
- Are you having a nice time?
- Um...

457
00:50:57,920 --> 00:51:01,515
- On your holiday?
- Yes, except we keep getting lost.

458
00:51:01,600 --> 00:51:03,591
Pull up a chair.

459
00:51:06,720 --> 00:51:08,233
Oh, my God.

460
00:51:08,320 --> 00:51:09,912
What?

461
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:15,472
Your clothes. I forgot.
I washed and dried them. I clean forgot.

462
00:51:15,560 --> 00:51:17,551
I must tell you where they are.

463
00:51:17,640 --> 00:51:20,632
But before I do you should tell him
what I told you.

464
00:51:20,720 --> 00:51:24,838
- What?
- What I did while you were both asleep.

465
00:51:24,920 --> 00:51:27,115
Oh. Right.

466
00:51:28,440 --> 00:51:32,592
Caroline came in and looked at us
both whilst we were asleep.

467
00:51:32,680 --> 00:51:34,398
Oh, did she?

468
00:51:35,720 --> 00:51:37,312
Yes.

469
00:51:38,480 --> 00:51:42,553
You were so peaceful.
Just like a baby.

470
00:51:43,720 --> 00:51:48,714
- Babies can be very ratty in their sleep.
- Oh, no, not him.

471
00:51:48,800 --> 00:51:53,669
- I'm sure he always sleeps sweetly.
- Yes, but I'm not a baby.

472
00:51:53,760 --> 00:51:58,038
I never said you were.
I only said that you slept like a baby.

473
00:51:58,120 --> 00:52:03,956
Now, listen. Robert is very keen for you
to stay and have dinner with us.

474
00:52:04,040 --> 00:52:07,715
He told me not to let you
have your clothes till you agreed.

475
00:52:09,160 --> 00:52:11,628
You must be starving, anyway.

476
00:52:12,600 --> 00:52:14,556
So you will?

477
00:52:15,960 --> 00:52:19,396
- Well, I...
- Oh, please. If you don't, he'll blame me.

478
00:52:19,480 --> 00:52:22,278
-  Let's stay.
- Oh, good.

479
00:52:25,000 --> 00:52:27,992
And... now can I have my clothes?

480
00:52:29,440 --> 00:52:34,116
They're locked in your
bathroom cupboard. Here's the key.

481
00:52:34,200 --> 00:52:37,078
- Thanks.
- Just through there.

482
00:52:42,120 --> 00:52:45,635
Isn't it sweet when men are shy?

483
00:52:45,720 --> 00:52:47,597
It's so sweet.

484
00:52:47,680 --> 00:52:50,240
Tell me, what do you do?
Do you work?

485
00:52:50,320 --> 00:52:56,111
Well, I mainly do voice-overs these days.
Commercials.

486
00:52:56,200 --> 00:52:59,749
I was with a women's group
until about six months ago.

487
00:52:59,840 --> 00:53:03,310
- What do you mean, a women's group?
- A theatre group.

488
00:53:03,400 --> 00:53:08,918
You're an actress?
What a beautiful thing that must be.

489
00:53:09,000 --> 00:53:12,436
Well, sometimes.
