We were expecting you sooner.

739
01:20:12,240 --> 01:20:15,038
- You got my message?
- No. When?

740
01:20:15,120 --> 01:20:18,715
I left a message at your hotel today.
We're going away, you see.

741
01:20:18,800 --> 01:20:21,837
- We didn't want to miss you.
- No, we didn't get it.

742
01:20:21,920 --> 01:20:24,912
But you came anyway. How wonderful.

743
01:20:26,320 --> 01:20:28,470
Going away?

744
01:20:28,560 --> 01:20:30,471
To Canada.

745
01:20:30,560 --> 01:20:35,714
To see my family, so we wanted
to say goodbye. Have a farewell drink.

746
01:20:35,800 --> 01:20:38,712
Give Mary some refreshment.
I have to go to my bar.

747
01:20:38,800 --> 01:20:41,917
I have business. Very quick.
Will you come with me?

748
01:20:42,000 --> 01:20:44,355
- I'll just...
- We won't be long.

749
01:20:44,440 --> 01:20:47,238
- Colin, I...
- Have you been swimming?

750
01:20:47,320 --> 01:20:48,912
Yes.

751
01:20:56,440 --> 01:20:58,431
Good God.

752
01:20:59,680 --> 01:21:03,593
- I thought you were going on holiday.
- We're selling up.

753
01:21:03,680 --> 01:21:08,390
We are going on holiday, but when we get
back we'll buy a ground-floor apartment.

754
01:21:08,480 --> 01:21:10,550
- That's what I need.
- Oh.

755
01:21:11,320 --> 01:21:15,108
- Would you like some herb tea?
- I'd love some.

756
01:21:33,160 --> 01:21:37,358
- <i>Ciao, Robert.</i>
- <i>Dove andate? Venite con noi.</i>

757
01:21:58,920 --> 01:22:03,357
- Somebody just pinched me.
- Venetians are very friendly people.

758
01:22:03,440 --> 01:22:05,431
This way.

759
01:22:12,480 --> 01:22:16,155
Robert said he told you
about his childhood.

760
01:22:17,080 --> 01:22:23,076
He exaggerates, you know. He turns
his past into stories to tell at the bar.

761
01:22:24,600 --> 01:22:28,832
- No sugar for me.
- I'm just stirring in the lemon.

762
01:22:28,920 --> 01:22:32,708
- Shall we take it out onto the terrace?
- May I?

763
01:22:35,000 --> 01:22:37,719
What happened to your back?

764
01:22:47,680 --> 01:22:50,433
<i>Sì, certo. È come hanno detto.</i>

765
01:22:50,520 --> 01:22:53,432
<i>Esattamente. Sì, sì, ho capito.</i>

766
01:22:53,520 --> 01:22:56,034
<i>Grazie. Allora posso stare tranquillo.</i>

767
01:22:56,120 --> 01:22:58,270
<i>Arrivederci.</i>

768
01:22:58,360 --> 01:23:01,955
<i>L'avvocato dice che il contratto è perfetto.</i>

769
01:23:15,640 --> 01:23:20,634
Did you understand what I was
telling people as we walked here?

770
01:23:21,440 --> 01:23:22,919
No.

771
01:23:23,000 --> 01:23:25,389
I was telling them that...

772
01:23:26,800 --> 01:23:32,796
you're my lover, and that Caroline
is jealous because she likes you too.

773
01:23:36,040 --> 01:23:39,430
- Why did you tell them that?
- Why "why"?

774
01:23:40,520 --> 01:23:42,795
We knew you would come back.

775
01:23:42,880 --> 01:23:46,350
Now, look here, Robert.
Hang on a minute.

776
01:23:49,960 --> 01:23:53,475
Why did you take that picture of me?
The one you showed Mary?

777
01:23:55,040 --> 01:23:58,510
- She's very quick.
- What was the point?

778
01:24:02,080 --> 01:24:04,150
I'm selling the bar.

779
01:24:04,240 --> 01:24:05,958
To him.

780
01:24:14,080 --> 01:24:18,870
I've never told anyone this - never -
but I want to tell you.

781
01:24:21,120 --> 01:24:26,797
Soon after we were married, Robert
started to hurt me when we made love.

782
01:24:26,880 --> 01:24:33,194
I tried to stop him, but he went on doing it.
And after a time, I found I liked it.

783
01:24:33,280 --> 01:24:40,834
Not the pain itself, but somehow...
the fact of being helpless before it.

784
01:24:42,520 --> 01:24:45,114
Being reduced to nothing by it.

785
01:24:45,880 --> 01:24:49,873
And of being punished,
therefore being guilty.

786
01:24:50,400 --> 01:24:54,075
I felt it was right that I should be punished.

787
01:24:56,080 --> 01:24:58,071
I thrilled to it.

788
01:24:59,920 --> 01:25:05,153
It took us over totally.
It grew and grew. It seemed never-ending.

789
01:25:06,000 --> 01:25:08,912
But there was an end to it.
We both knew what it was.

790
01:25:17,560 --> 01:25:20,358
That waiter was once a fisherman.

791
01:25:20,440 --> 01:25:25,833
But pollution has ruined the fish.
So fishermen become waiters.

792
01:25:30,600 --> 01:25:34,388
Why did you take my picture?
What does it mean?

793
01:25:37,440 --> 01:25:43,595
You see that barbershop? My grandfather
and my father used that barbershop.

794
01:25:43,680 --> 01:25:46,274
And I use that barbershop.

795
01:25:49,240 --> 01:25:51,310
That's Cemetery Island.

796
01:25:59,440 --> 01:26:02,955
My back happened suddenly one night.
It was very bad indeed.

797
01:26:03,040 --> 01:26:08,637
And there was an incompetent surgeon.
So I'm like this.

798
01:26:11,160 --> 01:26:13,720
He's terribly strong, you see.

799
01:26:13,800 --> 01:26:18,920
When he bent my head backwards
I blacked out with the pain,

800
01:26:19,000 --> 01:26:24,870
but I remember thinking
"It's going to happen. Now."

801
01:26:24,960 --> 01:26:29,112
"There's no going back on it.
It's going to happen now."

802
01:26:29,200 --> 01:26:32,317
"This is it. This is the end."

803
01:26:34,520 --> 01:26:36,238
I'm boring you.

804
01:26:37,720 --> 01:26:40,314
No, not at all. It's the...

805
01:26:41,480 --> 01:26:44,472
It's the sun, I think. The long swim.

806
01:26:48,520 --> 01:26:52,115
Do you and Colin do strange things?

807
01:26:54,640 --> 01:26:57,359
Oh, no, I don't think so. No.

808
01:26:57,880 --> 01:27:00,474
Oh, I'm sure Colin does.

809
01:27:01,440 --> 01:27:04,034
In fact, I'm certain he does.

810
01:27:05,040 --> 01:27:07,634
I want to show you something.

811
01:27:14,240 --> 01:27:17,710
- A bit dizzy.
- I must show you something.

812
01:27:35,880 --> 01:27:39,350
You haven't been in our bedroom,
have you?

813
01:27:40,840 --> 01:27:42,831
My legs ache.

814
01:28:05,560 --> 01:28:07,437
God!

815
01:28:07,520 --> 01:28:09,511
He's so beautiful.

816
01:28:11,360 --> 01:28:15,148
Robert saw you both
the first day you arrived.

817
01:28:15,880 --> 01:28:18,872
That was the first picture I saw of him.

818
01:28:18,960 --> 01:28:21,872
I'll never forget it.
Robert came home so excited.

819
01:28:21,960 --> 01:28:24,952
And then he brought
more and more photographs home.

820
01:28:25,040 --> 01:28:27,554
We became so close.

821
01:28:27,640 --> 01:28:29,835
Incredibly close.

822
01:28:29,920 --> 01:28:32,832
Colin brought us together.

823
01:28:32,920 --> 01:28:38,517
It was my idea to put him on the wall
so we could see him as we made love.

824
01:28:40,160 --> 01:28:43,152
I took that one myself. Isn't it brilliant?

825
01:28:43,240 --> 01:28:47,392
- Why?
- And then Robert brought you home.

826
01:28:48,200 --> 01:28:50,998
It was as if God was in on our dream.

827
01:28:53,320 --> 01:28:58,269
I knew fantasy was passing into reality.
Have you ever experienced that?

828
01:28:58,360 --> 01:29:01,272
It's like stepping into a mirror.

829
01:29:01,360 --> 01:29:02,918
Colin.

830
01:29:03,000 --> 01:29:05,594
Colin.

831
01:29:06,760 --> 01:29:09,911
- Wake up. Wake up.
-

832
01:29:10,000 --> 01:29:12,594
Colin and Robert are back.

833
01:29:15,000 --> 01:29:17,798
Do you know where we are now?

834
01:29:19,240 --> 01:29:21,231
Shall I tell you?

835
01:29:22,480 --> 01:29:25,950
We are on the other side of the mirror.

836
01:29:45,520 --> 01:29:47,590
Mary, what is it?

837
01:29:49,520 --> 01:29:51,795
Mary?

838
01:29:51,880 --> 01:29:53,950
What is it?

839
01:29:54,040 --> 01:29:58,511
What's the matter?
Mary. What's the matter?

840
01:29:59,400 --> 01:30:00,992
Cheers.

841
01:30:02,400 --> 01:30:06,518
- It's just a mild touch of sunstroke.
- She's not hot.

842
01:30:07,040 --> 01:30:09,508
What is it? Is it sunstroke?

843
01:30:09,600 --> 01:30:11,909
Tell me. Try to tell me.

844
01:30:12,000 --> 01:30:13,991
Tell me!

845
01:30:14,760 --> 01:30:16,637
- She's just tired.
- C...

846
01:30:16,720 --> 01:30:19,917
Are trying to say my name?

847
01:30:20,000 --> 01:30:22,958
- Co...
- What are you trying to say?

848
01:30:23,040 --> 01:30:25,395
- Co...
- Cold.

849
01:30:26,920 --> 01:30:30,674
- She's cold.
- We shouldn't crowd her.

850
01:30:30,760 --> 01:30:34,116
She needs a doctor.
Where's the telephone?

851
01:30:34,200 --> 01:30:36,395
It's been disconnected.

852
01:30:36,480 --> 01:30:39,756
- Disconnected?
- We're going away.

853
01:30:44,600 --> 01:30:47,637
You must know a doctor.

854
01:30:48,920 --> 01:30:52,151
Go and fetch a fucking doctor.
She's very ill!

855
01:30:54,440 --> 01:30:57,557
- No need to shout.
- She'll be fine.

856
01:30:58,600 --> 01:31:01,068
Mary understands.

857
01:31:01,760 --> 01:31:04,194
You understand too, don't you?

858
01:31:05,040 --> 01:31:08,999
You understand.
You do understand, don't you?

859
01:31:11,480 --> 01:31:14,870
Don't you know where you are? Get up!

860
01:31:19,440 --> 01:31:21,271
Don't move.

861
01:31:21,360 --> 01:31:24,079
You've cut my lip.

862
01:31:24,880 --> 01:31:26,472
Shh!

863
01:31:32,360 --> 01:31:34,828
What have you done to Mary?

864
01:31:35,680 --> 01:31:39,070
I'll do anything you want.
Just get a doctor for her.

865
01:31:39,160 --> 01:31:42,038
- What do you want?
- Want?

866
01:31:42,120 --> 01:31:45,237
I'll show you what we want.

867
01:31:45,320 --> 01:31:47,515
I'll show you.

868
01:31:55,080 --> 01:31:57,071
We'll show you.

869
01:33:00,560 --> 01:33:02,357
Carolina.

870
01:33:02,440 --> 01:33:04,237
Roberto.

871
01:33:24,880 --> 01:33:31,194
<i> What did you want</i>
<i>from these people? I ask you again.</i>

872
01:33:31,520 --> 01:33:34,432
What did you want from these people?

873
01:33:35,960 --> 01:33:38,349
Nothing. They were friends.

874
01:33:42,240 --> 01:33:44,231
Friends?

875
01:33:47,400 --> 01:33:49,595
We had dinner there.

876
01:33:50,640 --> 01:33:54,838
Why did you go back with your boyfriend
to these people?

877
01:33:55,720 --> 01:33:58,439
What did you want from them?

878
01:34:02,320 --> 01:34:05,392
Did your boyfriend like the woman?

879
01:34:07,560 --> 01:34:10,552
I liked her. I don't think that he...

880
01:34:11,960 --> 01:34:14,918
Did your boyfriend like the man?

881
01:34:15,800 --> 01:34:18,189
No. No, he didn't.

882
01:34:18,280 --> 01:34:20,350
And you?

883
01:34:20,840 --> 01:34:22,910
You liked the man?

884
01:34:23,000 --> 01:34:26,310
- Did you like the man?
- No.

885
01:34:26,400 --> 01:34:32,111
So, why did you go to dinner?
And why did you go back?

886
01:34:32,200 --> 01:34:36,591
Why did you come to Venice?
What were you looking for?

887
01:34:37,320 --> 01:34:42,348
- Nothing, we ju...
- Were you looking for... some fun?

888
01:34:45,160 --> 01:34:47,151
We were...

889
01:34:49,840 --> 01:34:52,434
We were going to get married.

890
01:35:00,360 --> 01:35:03,033
Is this the body of Colin Mayhew?

891
01:35:06,160 --> 01:35:08,151
Sign here.

892
01:35:18,600 --> 01:35:21,876
- Combed his hair the wrong way.
- Sorry?

893
01:35:23,680 --> 01:35:25,875
It doesn't go this way.

894
01:35:32,440 --> 01:35:34,431
It goes this way.

895
01:36:37,720 --> 01:36:41,633
...a tourist, but now
you plan everything in advance.

896
01:36:41,720 --> 01:36:47,113
You sell your bar, you sell your apartment,
you buy drug, and so on and so on.

897
01:36:47,200 --> 01:36:51,318
And then on the other hand you leave
your razor with your fingerprints,

898
01:36:51,400 --> 01:36:57,748
you book a ticket under your own name
and you travel with your own passport.

899
01:36:57,840 --> 01:36:59,717
We don't get it.

900
01:36:59,800 --> 01:37:02,473
Listen. Let me tell you something.

901
01:37:02,560 --> 01:37:06,678
My father was a very big man.

902
01:37:07,680 --> 01:37:11,434
All his life he wore a black moustache.

903
01:37:11,520 --> 01:37:15,638
When it turned grey
he used a little brush to keep it black,

904
01:37:15,720 --> 01:37:19,076
such as ladies use for their eyes.

905
01:37:19,160 --> 01:37:21,151
Mascara.

906
01:40:08,200 --> 01:40:10,668
Subtitles by Visiontext

907
01:40:12,520 --> 01:40:14,511
ENHOH

